 :tx/rationale "FIRST-PRINCIPLES PLAN REVISION — The dog-fooding feedback reveals that our plan optimizes for the WRONG metric. We have been optimizing for F(S) (formal verification status) and task count. But the feedback says: (1) F(S) is inert — doesn't respond to work. (2) Task titles are bloated — the observe→task pipeline produces verbose artifacts. (3) Ceremony cost is high — braid observe takes 3s per call. (4) Alert fatigue — harvest urgency fires too often. All four friction points share ONE root cause: the system optimizes for COMPLETENESS OF RECORDS rather than VELOCITY OF INSIGHT. Every feature we've built makes the store more complete (more datoms, more spec refs, more traces). But the agent's primary need is not completeness — it's ACTIVATION. The agent needs to be in the right cognitive state to produce correct output. The compile-to-prompt work (CTP-1..5) addresses this for seeds. But the same principle applies to EVERY touchpoint: status should activate, not just report. Observe should activate, not just record. The plan should be revised to make ACTIVATION QUALITY the primary metric, with completeness as a secondary effect."
